HACL* / Project Everest (cryptographic specifications)
================================================================

  Upstream:  https://github.com/hacl-star/hacl-star
  License:   Apache-2.0
  Used in:   crates/tls_core/src/crypto/*.ad{s,b}

  Every SPARK ghost function named `Spec_<Primitive>` in the
  crates/tls_core/src/crypto/ tree is a direct line-by-line port
  of an F* `let` definition from `Hacl.Spec.*.fst`, cited by
  file:line in the body comment. Specifically:

    Spec_SHA256       <- Hacl.Spec.SHA2.Generic.fst
    Spec_SHA384       <- Hacl.Spec.SHA2.Generic.fst
    Spec_SHA512       <- Hacl.Spec.SHA2.Generic.fst
    Spec_HMAC_*       <- Hacl.Spec.HMAC.fst
    Spec_HKDF_*       <- Hacl.Spec.HKDF.fst
    Spec_Chacha20     <- Hacl.Spec.Chacha20.fst
    Spec_Poly1305     <- Hacl.Spec.Poly1305.fst
    Spec_AES_*        <- Hacl.Spec.AES.fst
    Spec_GHASH        <- Hacl.Spec.GF128.fst
    Spec_GCM          <- Hacl.Spec.GCM.fst
    Spec_Scalar_Mult  <- Hacl.Spec.Curve25519.fst (X25519)
    Spec_Ed25519_*    <- Hacl.Spec.Ed25519.fst
    Spec_P256_*       <- Hacl.Spec.P256.fst
    Spec_ECDSA_P256_* <- Hacl.Spec.ECDSA.fst
    Spec_RSAPSS_*     <- Hacl.Spec.RSAPSS.fst

================================================================
miTLS / Project Everest (TLS protocol specifications)
================================================================

  Upstream:  https://github.com/project-everest/mitls-fstar
  License:   Apache-2.0
  Used in:   crates/tls_core/src/driver/*.ad{s,b}
             crates/tls_core/src/wire/*.ad{s,b}

  Contract structures (Pre/Post/invariant shapes) for the TLS
  1.3 handshake driver, record layer, and wire parsers are
  modelled after their miTLS counterparts. Each public
  procedure cites the miTLS source file in its `[VERIFIED — …]`
  header per docs/conventions.md §4.

================================================================
EverParse (parser combinator framework — pattern only)
================================================================

  Upstream:  https://github.com/project-everest/everparse
  License:   Apache-2.0

  The X.509 / DER walkers in crates/tls_core/src/wire/tls_core-cert*.ad{s,b}
  follow the EverParse "validate-then-extract" pattern; the code
  itself is hand-written SPARK, not a port.

================================================================
AdaCore RecordFlux (binary wire format DSL + generated SPARK)
================================================================

  Upstream:  https://github.com/AdaCore/RecordFlux
  License:   Apache-2.0
  Used in:   crates/*/specs/*.rflx (hand-written specs)
             crates/*/generated/rflx-*.ad{s,b}  (generated)

  All files under any crates/*/generated/rflx-* directory are
  output of the RecordFlux generator from the corresponding
  *.rflx spec in that crate's specs/ directory. The generated
  code carries its own Apache-2.0 header per RecordFlux's
  template.

================================================================
IANA registries (machine-derived enum tables)
================================================================

  Upstream:  https://www.iana.org/assignments/tls-parameters/
             https://www.iana.org/assignments/http2-parameters/
  License:   Public domain (IANA registry contents)
  Used in:   crates/tls_core/specs/tls-parameters.rflx
             crates/http2_core/specs/iana-http2-parameters.xml
             crates/http2_core/specs/http2_parameters.rflx

  The Frame_Type / Settings_Id / Alert_Description / Named_Group /
  Signature_Scheme / Cipher_Suite enums are machine-derived from
  the IANA XML registries via `rflx convert iana`. Re-run
  command captured in each crate's specs/README.md.

